This memorandum is a delegation of authorities under sections 552(c)(2) and 506(a)(1) of the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961. It grants the Secretary of State the authority to direct the drawdown of up to $25 million in commodities and services and up to $22 million in defense articles and services to provide immediate assistance to the Lebanese Armed Forces. The Secretary of State is also authorized to make the necessary congressional notification and determination for each drawdown. The memorandum is signed by President Joseph R. Biden Jr. and directs its publication in the Federal Register.